Conveys Mead's approval of program's work (see previous item); adds own congratulations and support.
Invites Watson to meeting of Computation Center to discuss plans for upcoming year. Attendees and date/time specified.

column8: Invitation to Mr. Watson and Other Corporation Members to a Review of the Program of the Computation Center, 3:00-5:00 p.m., Tuesday, March 4, 1958
column16: Suggests inviting Watson to meeting re Computation Center's progress; proposes further arrangements.
Thanks Morse and Computation Center for hospitality to self and IBM colleagues at recent meeting; congratulates MIT on progress.
Thanks Morse for invitation to participate in "Microminiaturization" session; covers speakers scheduled; hopes Morse will attend.
Thanks Fein for queries; notes areas as covered previously, and participants hence unavailable for seminar.
Solicits Morse's expression of interest to participate in WJCC session; see also items above in folder; next folder item enclosed.

column8: Form for expressions of interest in conference participation
column16: Form for expresion of interest (WJCC participation); enclosed with prior item.
Passes on Jay Forrester's suggestion of Wes Clark for TV series on computers.
Follows up on TV series; suggests several candidates as alternate "star" for David Huffman.
Follows up about TV series; suggests finding new star if needed.
Cover letter for WGBH letter (enclosed) regarding series on computers; hopes to work out possibility.
Expresses WGBH's strong interest in producing series on computers; notes accommodations will be made for MIT personnel as needed.

column8: Memo on Discussion of Computer Series at WGBH
column16: Outlines $100,000 grant request from National Educational TV Center in Michigan for MIT to produce 20-part series about computers.
Asks Young's advice as UT Austin CC director about convening Director's meetings.
Responds to inquiry about CC progress with enclosed report of activities (not in folder).
